Usually, samples from the respiratory tract are taken for diagnostic purposes. These include swabs from nose or throat, nasopharyngeal aspirates, nasal washes, sputum, bronchial aspirates, and bronchoalveolar lavages. Upon infection with HPeVs or HAdVs systemic infections or other complications, e.g., gastrointestinal or neurological symptoms, may occur. In this case, additional specimens, ranging from stool, blood, urine, and cerebrospinal fluid, are taken (
 Olijve et al., 2018; 
 Khanal et al., 2018).
